# Request Logging Conventions

Use a single `morgan`-style middleware mounted before routes.

## Rules

- Log `method`, `path`, `status`, and response time in ms.
- One line per request; no multi-line entries.
- Never log request bodies or headers (they may contain secrets).
- Use `tiny` format in test, `combined` in production.

## Example

```js
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  const t = Date.now();
  res.on('finish', () => {
    console.log(`${req.method} ${req.path} ${res.statusCode} ${Date.now() - t}ms`);
  });
  next();
});
```
